Minimalist Design Blog














0





















FurnitureTom BoxOctober 05, 2016Dmitry Kozinenko


Field
FurnitureTom BoxOctober 05, 2016Dmitry Kozinenko






Designed by Dmitry KozinenkoField, a minimalist shelf, has been designed by Ukrainian product designer Dmitry Kozinenko. Creating the illusion that all the objects upon the shelf effortlessly float within when viewed from the front. Built with simple metal rods bent in a way that offers a platform for objects to be stacked upon. Built in both black and white, the shelf is built to a modest dimension allowing for the unit to be placed against a wall at a specific angle. 




























Tom Box
Founder of John & Douglas and a passionate advocate for minimalist product, architecture, interior and furniture design. 







