                                                    Tesla's Model 3 will be launched with panache--and a party--later Friday
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    1:24 PM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


Electric car maker's mass-market sedan will finally see the light of day. Tesla Inc. (TSLA) will hand over the first few Model 3 s at a launch party later Friday. Several analysts have received an invitation for the event, which will be live-streamed on the company's website.

















                                                    Tesla earnings: Will Model 3 live up to the hype?
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    10:29 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


Wall Street to zero in on production timeline. Tesla Inc. (TSLA) is scheduled to report second-quarter results after the market close on Aug. 2.. Wall Street expects another loss for Silicon Valley company, but that is unlikely to matter much.

















                                                    New rule forces big car makers into big changes in how they count revenues
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    10:26 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


Tesla still tight-lipped about impact, GM admits it could be nearly $1 billion, and Ford gets a jump on things with minimal net impact. The new revenue recognition rule is dramatically changing the way automotive manufacturers like General Motors Co. (GM), Tesla Inc. (TSLA), and Ford Motor Co. (F) record revenues for everything from rental car fleet leases to marketing incentives like resale value guarantees, cash rebates, volume rebates and product warranties. Read: A revenue rule change is...

















                                                    GM Cadillac chief outlines plan for fewer sedans, more electrics
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    1:59 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


The head of General Motors Co's Cadillac luxury division said on Thursday the brand will shrink its lineup of sedans and expand its offerings of sport utility vehicles and hybrid and electric vehicles in response to market shifts.

















                                                    PRESS DIGEST - Wall Street Journal - July 28
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    12:16 AM ET 07/28/2017
                                                


The following are the top stories in the Wall Street Journal. - GOP leaders struggled to overcome tensions between House and Senate Republicans that threatened to derail a slimmed-down health-law repeal, the party's last-ditch effort to deliver on their promise to overhaul the Affordable Care Act.

















