                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    4:56 PM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


The head of General Motors Co's Cadillac luxury division said on Thursday the brand will shrink its lineup of sedans and expand its offerings of sport utility vehicles and hybrid and electric vehicles in response to market shifts.

















                                                    U.S. House panel approves legislation to speed deployment of self-driving cars
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    11:48 AM ET 07/27/2017
                                                


An influential U.S. House Committee on Thursday approved a revised bipartisan bill on a 54-0 vote that would speed the deployment of self-driving cars without human controls and bar states from blocking autonomous vehicles.

















                                                    Some Chinese electric car makers mull alliance to save money, time
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    7:00 PM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


* Signs that nascent EV industry already consolidating. * EV start-ups aim joint development of car platform. * Start-ups aim to seal deal JV deal by end-September. * WM Motor says interested, but unlikely to join for now. By Norihiko Shirouzu.

















                                                    Elon Musk just burned Mark Zuckerberg in a tweet about AI
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    7:19 AM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


Tesla CEO calls Facebook (FB) founder's understanding of AI' limited'. "Robocalypse," or a force for good? Tesla Inc. CEO Elon Musk and Facebook (FB) founder and CEO Mark Zuckerberg traded barbs this week over artificial intelligence, with Musk tweeting the latest salvo earlier Tuesday:.

















                                                    Tesla Model S back at the top at Consumer Reports
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    7:19 AM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


Luxury sedan regains top safety marks. Tesla Inc.' s luxury sedan is back in the good graces of Consumer Reports. The Model S regained its status as the magazine's top-rated, ultra-luxury sedan after Tesla updated its software to include automatic emergency braking at highway speeds, Consumer Reports said Tuesday.

















                                                    Geek fight! Musk says Zuckerberg naive about killer robots
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    2:25 PM ET 07/25/2017
                                                


Silicon Valley baron Elon Musk insulted rival billionaire Mark Zuckerberg on Tuesday, escalating a tech wizard war of words over whether robots will become smart enough to kill their human creators.

















                                                    Tesla Model S regains top rating after software update -Consumer Reports
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    11:05 AM ET 07/25/2017
                                                


Tesla Inc's Model S sedan regained Consumer Reports' top rating in its vehicle class, the magazine said on Tuesday, after the automaker updated the emergency braking system on the vehicle. Tesla provided an over-the-air update in July to its software on the Model S to include automatic emergency braking at highway speeds, Consumer Reports said.

















                                                    Lyft accelerates efforts to develop self-driving cars
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    11:00 AM ET 07/21/2017
                                                


Lyft Inc has formed a self-driving car division, company executives said, a bold investment for the second-largest U.S. ride-services firm as it jockeys for position in the highly competitive autonomous vehicle race. The executives said on Thursday the company would soon open a facility in Palo Alto, California, that would eventually be staffed by "several hundred" engineers.

















                                                    Citi goes neutral on Tesla stock, but counts itself in bull camp
                                                


                                                    MarketWatch – 
                                                    10:58 AM ET 07/21/2017
                                                


Tesla is a leader, but best wait for better entry point, analysts say. Analysts at Citi decided to split the difference between bulls and bears on Tesla Inc. (TSLA) stock, initiating their coverage with a neutral rating. Tesla is a leader in "car of the future" initiatives, including shared mobility and driverless cars, and its product success, brand appeal, and other positive attributes can't be denied, the analysts wrote in a note this week.

















                                                    PRESS DIGEST- New York Times business news - July 21
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    1:40 AM ET 07/21/2017
                                                


The following are the top stories on the New York Times business pages. - U.S. President Donald Trump's administration said Harley-Davidson (HOG) was no longer required to fund the antipollution program, knocking $3 million off the company's bill. http://nyti.ms/2gP7fwp. - Microsoft (MSFT) reported that its profit in the most recent quarter more than doubled from a year ago.

















                                                    PRESS DIGEST- Wall Street Journal - July 21
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    12:18 AM ET 07/21/2017
                                                


The following are the top stories in the Wall Street Journal. - The U.S. Treasury Department on Thursday imposed a $2 million fine on Exxon Mobil Corp (XOM) for what it called a "reckless disregard" of U.S. sanctions on Russia while Secretary of State Rex Tillerson was the oil giant's chief executive, a finding the company immediately said it would challenge. http://on.wsj.com/2uFgiFZ.

















